<br>
Then, the alarm clock I carry in my bag went off. <br>
<br>
Turned around, to see an extremely groggy prismatic dragon complaining about &quot;turning that noise off.&quot; He was in a fairly decent mood, since there hadn't been a major battle to wake him up, just a alarm. I shared two stacks of frost giant steaks with him, and spotted him some Fizzlecutter that I'd bought from Jhary.<br>
<br>
We chatted for a bit, and he said he had to go, something about business with Veeshan. Then he flew off. As I waved goodbye to him, I thought to myself, &quot;y'know, for the alleged destroyer of Norrath, he's not a bad guy.&quot; Then I collected the uber loot underneath him: 2 cp and a rusty rapier.<br>
<br>
Anyway, sorry everyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uikonoclastiafv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IkonoclastiaFV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/29/02 7:39:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2773.topic&index=118>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Okay, the truth must be told</span><hr size=1> Selfish and Childish and no amount of &quot;the new revamped ST blah blah sales pitch&quot; will change that.  The fact is you've  denied everyone who was intending to see the warders and attempt to obtain some of the unique loot from ST the chance to do so.<br>
